job description
square is seeking a highly seasoned risk operations manager to join our dynamic risk operation team in this role you will provide support for the development implementation and documentation of innovative fraud prevention strategy by analyzing large set of transactional data this position will also work closely with product strategy managers data scientists and engineers to identify and evaluate fraud risk on card deposit and ach payment in addition this role oversees system and analytical tool enhancement in order to maintain productivity and efficiency of risk strategy importantly this role will represent the team a a member of squares high impact cross-functional team that support initiative for both existing and emerging payment product this position requires an in-depth understanding of the principle of both account and portfolio level risk management
you will
lead a team of 8 high performing investigator in a fast- paced environment including performance management coaching developing and driving the vision for the team
build team manage recruiting effort and partner with talent team to bring in top quality candidate to fill critical role
identifies risk factor and trend of potentially fraudulent activity utilizing technical data analysis and statistical interpretation
develop and implement comprehensive fraud detection strategy and business rule that balance fraud loss cost of execution and customer experience
leads root cause analysis to identify opportunity to predict prevent and mitigate risk within process and performance
utilize analytics to optimize existing fraud strategy in order to reduce false positive rate and increase fraud detection rate
extract and analyze data investigate data integrity generate metric and perform data and portfolio analysis
generate fraud metric to show the performance of fraud system for use in management reporting
identify gap in current system policy and strategy and take action to mitigate emerging fraud risk with guidance from manager
manages multiple project to enhance and optimize fraud strategy system and tool
develops trending report and key indicator to serve a early warning risk indicator for potentially fraudulent activity
partners with internal partner across the company to effect change and promote awareness through the coordination of fraud detection monitoring of system enhancement and statistical trend analysis
qualifications
you have
mba or ms degree in finance analytics or mathematics or bachelors degree in mathematics analytics or criminology preferred
5 year management experience
experience mitigating online fraud such a account takeover phishing online card testing etc
strong quantitative analytical experience including background with statistical modeling analysis
ability to analyze large transactional datasets interpret ambiguous situation and make decision under pressure
deep understanding of the online payment landscape across all participant issuer merchant acquirer and network
skills in sql crm and data analysis tool is a plus
excellent written oral and presentation skill and an ability to synthesize information and make clear concise recommendation on a course of action
creative team-focused and effective problem solve
cfe or aap preferred
